My education didn't include any art or even any technical drafting classes so
I've really just been winging it with some dusty books. But luckily art is a
well-studied subject and we've figured out perspective, realism and almost
everything already so I don't think I need a formal class, just some nudging
here and there from friends who know better than I.

For instance I was recently gifted a set of 48 oil paints but was advised by a
friend to only use a few, otherwise I'd be spoiled by being able to select the
exact color instead of mixing the primary colors and understanding the theory.
